# SPEC DEVELOPMENT RULES
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## When Creating Specs:
- Use examples from real usage (not invented)
- Define grammar precisely
- Show both correct and incorrect usage
- Explain WHY rules exist (not just WHAT they are)
- Version all specs (proto.v10, v11, etc.)

## Spec Structure:
1. Purpose statement
2. Grammar definition
3. Symbol reference
4. Usage patterns
5. Examples
6. Anti-patterns
7. Validation rules

